        "authorId" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "body" : "To avoid issues on `OS X` we try to use\n\n``` yaml\n        - libgcc  # [linux]\n        - libgfortran  # [osx]\n```\n\nWhen Fortran (and `libquadmath`) is needed. If you also need `libgomp` then you can remove leave as is.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-11-17T19:33:38Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-11-17T19:42:37Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "0c3a15f7-e76f-420e-bb74-57862be380c4",
        "parentId" : "c599daa8-fae2-400b-aa46-25b55a3d3942",
        "authorId" : "50a2616f-cd96-418b-bb5c-dfa623bd908e",
        "body" : "We actually do need `libgomp`, so should we just leave it as `libgcc` and remove `libgfortran`?\n\nWhat are the issues that can occur on OS X?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-11-17T19:56:04Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-11-17T19:56:04Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "50a2616f-cd96-418b-bb5c-dfa623bd908e",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "70ae1e79-bc9b-469a-b8de-0d654653c124",
        "parentId" : "c599daa8-fae2-400b-aa46-25b55a3d3942",
        "authorId" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "body" : "> We actually do need libgomp, so should we just leave it as libgcc and remove libgfortran?\n\nExactly.\n\n> What are the issues that can occur on OS X?\n\nOther packages may pick up `libstdc++` and, if they are using `clang`'s `libc++` they may break. But I do not think anyone will build anything against `ncl`, so this is probably safe.\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-11-17T20:10:38Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-11-17T20:10:38Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ed861b6f-1f9b-4be3-9da8-c8c844648413",
        "tags" : [
